The paper proposes a new variant of the Wasserstein distance that is robust in high-dimensional settings, and provides algorithms to compute it. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), or Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
